  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development, by reason of its roof pitch, height, scale, depth, width, siting, fenestration, and proximity to neighbouring habitable room windows, would result in a marked and harmful loss of the symmetry shared between the host building and 32 Drayton Road, would represent an overbearing and discordant form of development, would detract from the appearance of the dwelling, and would result in a loss of light, outlook and privacy to 30 Drayton Road. The development would therefore run contrary to the NPPF (2021), policies D3, D4 and D6 of the London Plan (2021), policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Ealing SPD4."
